   ↓
Extract User ID

How does your backend know which user is making the request?

During login I generate a JWT containing the user's id. The frontend sends that token in the Authorization header. My auth middleware verifies the token and extracts the userId, then attaches it to req.userId. Every protected route uses that value.

How do you ensure users only modify their own transactions?

Transaction.findOneAndUpdate(
  {
    _id: req.params.id,
    user: req.userId
  },
  req.body,
  { new: true }
);
User A's token
      ↓
req.userId
      ↓
Only documents owned by that user can be updated'

