Database Design
User Collection
{
  _id,
  name,
  email,
  password,
  createdAt
}
Transaction Collection
{
  _id,
  user,
  title,
  amount,
  type,
  category,
  date,
  createdAt
}
Relationship

One user can have many transactions.

User 1 ──────── Many Transactions

Transaction stores user id:

user: req.user.id

This is the most important part.
If you forget this, your app is broken from a security point of view.

Mongoose Queries

Find user:

User.findOne({ email });

Create user:

User.create({ name, email, password: hashedPassword });

Get user transactions:

Transaction.find({ user: req.user.id });

Update transaction:

Transaction.findOneAndUpdate(
  { _id: req.params.id, user: req.user.id },
  req.body,
  { new: true }
);

Delete transaction:

Transaction.findOneAndDelete({
  _id: req.params.id,
  user: req.user.id
});

Notice this:

user: req.user.id

That prevents users from editing/deleting others’ transactions.









